    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Despite the great number of reports about the efficacy of oestrogens or antimuscarinics on
      OAB symptoms, so far no author has tried to investigate whether the concomitant
      administration of these two drugs, acting on two different pathophysiological mechanisms,
      could have a synergic effect reducing the rate of non-responders to treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
